During creation it's tested with the latest version of google chrome. Many features such as save files won't worry correctly in private browsing mode or on privacy focused browsers. Known Issues: - Because of the new challenge rating system, some of the home weight lifting descriptions are incongruent with the size of the home gym. For example, you might have the level 1 weights, and get a scene describing her lifting weights from a later set. - There's also some general incongruency in descriptions throughout the game. This is because when I first made it years ago, level 20 was supposed to be the "peak human", with everything above it being supernatural. But but over time 'peak human' has shifted to somewhere in the level 25-30 mark, with 30+ being superhuman. - Intelligence development is a little wonky. It will eventually be revamped and expanded with the Focus + Willpower update. - Flexibility, Reaction Speed, and Beauty are all underdeveloped. - Jobs and earning money in general are underdeveloped. "I feel great babe! Maybe we should do something fun now that we're recharged?" <<LevelUp "both">><<if $display is "notes">> Original Notes for Stamina Update: - Stamina stat introduced. It's used for performing physical exp-gaining activities. The current stamina formula is: maxstam = 2 + (endurance * 1.5) rounded. - Stamina is recovered by sleeping, using the 'do nothing' activity, drinking StamAids, and using the Restoration Chamber. - Experience revamped. Activities now have a 'challenge rating' for each attribute they challenge. As long as a character's attribute is below this 'challenge rating', they will receive full EXP towards that attribute. The base rate is 10 EXP. Each attribute level over the challenge rating will give diminishing returns on experience (-10% diminishing returns per level, until no more experience is gained when the attribute is more than 10 over the challenge rating) - Base experience is 10 EXP per activity, though the girlfriend starts off with a 'gifted' perk that boosts exp gain on all activities. Supplements boost strength + endurance exp, and girlfriend 'evolutions' now boost all activity exp. - Intelligence revamped slightly. Uses the new EXP system, meaning you can now actually gain more than just a couple levels of intelligence from each activity. - Time system revamped, now uses minutes. - Activities have different time amounts now. - Characters no longer have to go to bed by midnight. They do still need to sleep (or use a restoration chamber) to level up. - New item StamAid recovers some stamina. Can be purchased from the StamAid vending machine at the shopping center. - New apartment upgrade at Ulric's, the treadmill. Has an Endurance Challenge Rating of 20, and a strength rating of 1. - New equipment, the Brain Teaser. Very powerful item that will passively give the wearer Intelligence EXP during activities. Purchasable at Alison's and currently wearable by GF. - New activity, Walking. Has an endurance CR of 3, but a very low stamina cost. Useful for training endurance early game. Has a slightly higher rate of finding items than running (reasoning being you're going slower so it would be easier to spot items) - New Creation, Restoration Chamber. Revitalizes all stamina for a character and levels up attributes if the exp requirement is met. - Do Stuff Together menu revamped - Workout analyzer revamped - Characters can go to sleep independently in the split up menu. Rest for 4 hours option removed. - Wrist/Ankle weights now add 5 strength/endurance challenge rating to exercise activities respectively. - Most things are cheaper, especially the creations. - MegaBatteries now increase by $50 per purchased instead of $200 - New Advanced Fiction and Advanced Nonfiction books to further train intelligence - Brain Blaster revamped. Can now be purchased from Ulric OR created (created costs less but requires INT). No longer uses batteries. Now trains intelligence regularly with new exp system, challenge rating of 30. - Atrophy occurs a little slower since characters will be probably be sleeping more often. - Split up characters can now wait until the other is finished with their activity. - Game now uses the memorize function to store whether the game is cleared inside the browser's metadata. - - - Current plans for Upcoming Versions (You can expect a few of these in each upcoming update): Next Update: - Story Scenes that trigger upon meeting certain criteria - Expanded Transfer/Schmo scenarios Future Updates: Important System/Structural changes to the game: - Career Overhaul, new jobs and revamped money balancing - Perks, Skills, and Character Creation - Scenes that play based on meeting stats/criteria - Girlfriend personality and randomized dialogue - Luck, magic, and fame. Planned Content additions: - Many more descriptions. - More competitions - Main quest and revamped goddess chamber - New creations - Locations - Expanded NPCs with stats that change based on player actions - Community College Fun / Flavor - Expanded Endings - Achievements - New Game+ Mod Stuff: -Events Events have been changed to be more involved and complex than before. The reason for this is to make events more than big stats = win, although big enough stats will basically automatically win you any event. To add more depth, the competition events have more mechanics to keep in mind when competing, allowing you to win even when you are lacking the skills or stats compared to the competition (to a certain extent). Prizes are randomly picked from a pool and scale to the difficulty of the event. Certain events have date and time requirements, meaning they can only be accessed during a specific time window. Not only that but you must know about the event and register in order to attend, although this rule only applies to particular events. You can wait for events to start by going somewhere. As long as you know about an event, you can usually register AT the event and don't have to register ahead of time. Try it out and get a handle of it first before voicing your thoughts, concerns, or any changes needed to these. -Two new events: Powerlifting Competition and the Science Fair -Powerlifting: Outlift the competition in a test of strength; the most straight forward of all the events. -Science Fair: A bit more dynamic, you and your girlfriend can browse, shop, and compete in a science-based fair requiring a level of strategy. -Returning events includes: Allison's Sale, and Mystique's Magical Mercantile. -For now, all events are randomly generated. Scheduled events with fixed levels of difficulty, fixed prizes, and set dates are planned to be included so you don't have to rely on rng. Depending on the reception of the more dynamic events, it will influence the direction of the two other events I am still working on, the race and bodybuilding competition events. -The Equipment Menu now has an option to save an outfit. You can save up to five different outfits per character, are able name the saved outfit, and quickly swap into any of these at any time from the Equipment Menu. For gameplay reasons, when saving clothing, their stats will reflect what you have at point of swapping and not when you saved them. -All clothing and equipment now have stats referred to as "clothing stats". These stats influence the experience multiplier when doing activities such as running or working out, providing purpose to clothing and incentive to choose appropriate outfits during certain activities. However, this is optional and must be turned on in the advanced options menu during game start up. This option is turned off by default. -Clothing can now have four enchantments at a time compared to just two. -Enchanted books now have no limit for their level compared to the previous maximum of just level two. -Growth enchantments changed so that they now influence the challenge rating of activities by lowering them to improve the amount of exp you earn. -The sew machine is now called the Equipment Enhancer. It operates the same as before but also has three new features: Enchantment Book Combination, Clothing Stat Upgrades, and able to check clothing stats per equip. -Combine two books of the same type to create a higher level book. No limit to spell level as mentioned above allowing the creation of ridiculously leveled enchantments. This still requires the use of a MegaBattery as every other function of this machine does. -Upgrade the stats of your equipment and clothing to be more effective by using the appropriate focusing crystal to increase its stats. -The Equipment Enhancer has view the stats of clothing/equipment without the need of a MegaBattery. -Internet: The Internet is an activity you can do together which serves as the way of finding and knowing about events as well as offering other novelties. -The Index is a (experimental) catalog found on the internet that provides in-depth information, clues, and strategies for game mechanics that these change notes do not usually cover. The Index is a method of getting elaborative advice for particular mechanics for the respective index page. This is currently in testing and may be removed if its purpose is too niche. It is restricted to new content mostly. To clarify, the Index is a referral you can use to discover new or hidden elements in the game. It is not required to use at all and not intended to replace these notes or justify a lack of explaination. You can always ask me on how something works if you want to know how something works. This is a (experimental) method of giving guidance and rewarding to players who want to find the deeper layers of the mod stuff without having to list every small detail in the change log. Hopefully it's of use to you during your playthrough, though it is limited for now to just the new, complicated stuff. As I said before, if this feature isn't that useful, I will remove it. -For now, the debug menu, and closing of the shopping mall on Sunday are turned off for testing purposes for this snapshot, particularly the events. -Small grammar and spelling fixes including formatting fixes. Not included in this mod: -The ability to change jobs. I have not altered or changed anything regarding jobs despite the previous mod's additions and changes. I am waiting to include these as I want to think more about the changes I want to add as well as wait and see if MagnusMagneto does anything to the jobs in the near future so I don't have to rewrite the whole code from scratch. -Job Change Event not included. Obviously because there are no jobs to change to so the job change event is not included in the returning event list. -Peter Special Sale Item Event Nothing currently planned to add this event as its purpose was to provide the upgrade parts, which is now available in other ways. -Old ending to the mod is not included as the new ending serves the purpose the old one did. -Relationship values are not used or included although still changeable in the debug menu. The relationship value is to be improved and added. -Old living room dialogue is removed to be improved or mixed with the official game living room dialogues at a later date. -The player can no longer wear the amulets worn by the girlfriend. <<endif>>\ <<if $display is "thanks">> Writing, scripting, design, etc. - [[MagnusMagneto|https://www.deviantart.com/magnusmagneto]] Art by Oriander2000 and Ritualist Compare Physique descriptions by Oriander2000 Custom Macros by ChapelL GF height code from stupiddoritosbag Life Sim mod Image resizing code by UnknownUsername33 and hiev Made in [[Twine|http://twinery.org]] with [[Sugarcube 2|https://www.motoslave.net/sugarcube/2/]] featuring the Bleached stylesheet. !!!!!Contact: MagnusMagneto23@gmail.com Special thanks to the following people for their generous contributions! The main focus, being the building competition, allows a level of strategy when deciding to build your design. The safest strategy is building something simple over a more complex machine, then filling the gaps with the secondary features, but trying not to go over the timer of 60 minutes to not get penalized. It is way more punishing to have an incomplete design no matter how advanced or how many features, although there are a few times you may want to opt for an incomplete design because of the following mechanics. It is most important that your main design above all else is finished as the bulk of your points is rated based on if it is finished or not. Also, any secondary features you had will ALL be incomplete if you don't finish the main design, even by mere minutes. You will gain partial credit if you pass the 60 minute timer by either main or secondary design. Some secondary features have passive abilities and advantages, but you MUST NOT pass the build timer or else your features will be incomplete and NOT have their abilities. Another layer of consideration for your main design is of your competition as their decisions can influence your score. If you and your competition choose and repeat the same design (you choose simple and 30% chooses simple for example), you will all be penalized. Although the decisions of the competition is randomly decided, you can generally figure out the complexity the competition will choose by the difficulty level of the event where higher levels go for the complex and advanced sets while lower levels aim for the simple design. The creative feature completely ignores this mechanic and does not penalize you even if you were to be penalized.
